Well, I'm late on this train, but it's funny that you mention /co/ and MLPG, because I used to drawfag there. That thread is actually the reason I picked up drawing in the first place, back in late 2010. I still have fond memories of that place and I'm glad I lent them my services.

I don't know if it was /co/ culture or if 4chan was more appreciative back then, but we appreciated the shit out of contributors. It was a great community to be a part of and it constantly spurred you to start creating yourself. We had dozens (literally dozens) of people who started drawing because of the friendly, encouraging and inspiring atmosphere and that also invited artists who were already pretty good.

Artists went out of their way to contribute quality work and Anons went out of their way to be grateful. It was very pleasant to make stuff there and then have a bunch of people reply telling you they enjoyed it.

In those early years we received so much stuff and had so many good artists that basically every single thread was filled with the equal value of $100-500 in artist commission money.

Things went to shit in 2013, but I still think it is a good reminder for /hmofa/ to not take our contributors for granted. If you ignore contributions it will make the artist or writer feel unwelcome and like a failure and if that happens one time too often they'll leave and never come back.
